  "text": "JavaScript parsing and bytecode compilation in SpiderMonkey follows this pipeline:\n\n**1. Entry Point - BytecodeCompiler (js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.h/.cpp)**\nPublic API functions like `CompileGlobalScript()`, `CompileEvalScript()`, and `CompileModule()` are the entry points. These functions initialize compilation state, create a ScriptCompiler instance, and orchestrate the entire parsing and compilation process. The main compilation routine is in `CompileGlobalScriptToStencilAndMaybeInstantiate()` which delegates to `ScriptCompiler<Unit>::compile()`.\n\n**2. Parser Entry Point - Parser (js/src/frontend/Parser.h/.cpp)**\nThe `Parser` class (and base `GeneralParser` class) implements the JavaScript parser. Key entry methods include:\n- `globalBody(GlobalSharedContext*)` - parses global scope scripts\n- `evalBody(EvalSharedContext*)` - parses eval scope scripts  \n- These methods tokenize and parse source text, returning a `ParseNode` AST tree\n\n**3. AST Node Types - ParseNode (js/src/frontend/ParseNode.h)**\nThe abstract syntax tree is represented by the `ParseNode` class hierarchy. All node types are defined through the `FOR_EACH_PARSE_NODE_KIND` macro, which generates binary nodes (BinaryNode), unary nodes (UnaryNode), ternary nodes (TernaryNode), list nodes (ListNode), and specialized nodes like FunctionNode, ModuleNode, CallNode, etc. Each node type corresponds to JavaScript language constructs.\n\n**4. Bytecode Emission - BytecodeEmitter (js/src/frontend/BytecodeEmitter.h/.cpp)**\nAfter parsing, the `BytecodeEmitter` class takes the ParseNode AST and generates bytecode. The main entry point is `emitScript(ParseNode* body)`. The emitter walks the AST and generates a sequence of bytecode instructions stored in `BytecodeSection`. Specialized emitter classes handle specific constructs (CallOrNewEmitter, FunctionEmitter, IfEmitter, etc.).\n\n**5. Bytecode Storage - CompilationStencil (js/src/frontend/CompilationStencil.h)**\nThe generated bytecode is stored in a `CompilationStencil` structure which contains:\n- `scriptData`: ScriptStencil entries for all scripts\n- `scriptExtra`: ScriptStencilExtra for immutable metadata  \n- `sharedData`: SharedDataContainer holding the actual bytecode via SharedImmutableScriptData\n- `gcThingData`: References to garbage-collected objects used by bytecode\n- `scopeData`: Scope and binding information\n\n**6. JSScript Bytecode Object - JSScript (js/src/vm/JSScript.h)**\nThe stencil is converted to the runtime `JSScript` class via `JSScript::fromStencil()`. JSScript inherits from BaseScript and contains the compiled bytecode. The actual bytecode bytes are accessed via `code()` method, which returns a pointer to `jsbytecode*` from the underlying `ImmutableScriptData`.\n\n**Pipeline Summary:**\nSource Text → Parser (globalBody/evalBody) → ParseNode AST → BytecodeEmitter (emitScript) → CompilationStencil (sharedData) → JSScript (code()) → Bytecode execution"
}

